to be described with a density

00:48:28.850 --> 00:48:29.810
matrix.

00:48:29.810 --> 00:48:32.690
Or in other words, if you have
a coherent superposition between

00:48:32.690 --> 00:48:36.250
excited and ground state, you
cannot just say spontaneous

00:48:36.250 --> 00:48:40.730
emission is now increasing the
amplitude to be in the ground

00:48:40.730 --> 00:48:41.300
state.

00:48:41.300 --> 00:48:43.820
It really does something
fundamentally different.

00:48:43.820 --> 00:48:47.870
It puts population into the
ground state with-- I'm loosely

00:48:47.870 --> 00:48:50.110
speaking now, but
with a random phase.

00:48:50.110 --> 00:48:52.470
And this can only be
described probabilistically

00:48:52.470 --> 00:48:54.820
by using the density matrix.

00:48:54.820 --> 00:48:57.562
But what you are talking
about is actually,

00:48:57.562 --> 00:48:59.520
