I know that a discussion of
the hydrogen atom, the solution

01:00:20.360 --> 01:00:22.820
of the Schrodinger equation
for the hydrogen atom

01:00:22.820 --> 01:00:24.670
is in all quantum
mechanics textbooks.

01:00:24.670 --> 01:00:26.300
I'm not doing it here.

01:00:26.300 --> 01:00:29.840
I rather want to give you
a few insightful comments

01:00:29.840 --> 01:00:36.040
about the structure of hydrogen,
some scaling of length scales

01:00:36.040 --> 01:00:37.860
and energy levels,
because this is

01:00:37.860 --> 01:00:40.690
something we need
later in the course.

01:00:40.690 --> 01:00:43.450
So in other words, I want to
highlight a few things which

01:00:43.450 --> 01:00:46.790
are often not emphasized
in the textbook.

01:00:46.790 --> 01:00:48.879
So let's talk about
the hydrogen atom.

01:00:58.460 --> 01:01:03.630
So the energy levels
of the hydrogen atom

01:01:03.630 --> 01:01:05.400
are described by
the Rydberg formula.

01:01:09.670 --> 01:01:15.100
This actually follows already
from the simple Bohr model.

01:01:15.100 --> 01:01:19.170
But of course, also from
the Schrodinger equation.

01:01:19.170 --> 01:01:29.150
And it says that
the energy levels--

01:01:29.150 --> 01:01:31.070
let me write it in
the following way.

01:01:33.620 --> 01:01:39.100
It depends on the electron
mass, the electron charge, h bar

01:01:39.100 --> 01:01:40.820
square.

01:01:40.820 --> 01:01:48.890
It has a reduced
mass correction.

01:01:48.890 --> 01:01:52.500
And then, n is the
principal quantum number.

01:01:52.500 --> 01:01:54.250
It scales as 1 over n squared.

01:01:57.610 --> 01:02:05.770
So this here is the
reduced mass factor.

01:02:05.770 --> 01:02:11.740
This here is called the
Rydberg constant R, sometimes

01:02:11.740 --> 01:02:16.400
with the index infinity
because it is the Rydberg

01:02:16.400 --> 01:02:19.840
constant which describes the
spectrum of a hydrogen atom

01:02:19.840 --> 01:02:23.880
where the nucleus
has infinite mass.

01:02:23.880 --> 01:02:30.790
If you include the
reduced mass correction

01:02:30.790 --> 01:02:35.650
for the mass of the
proton, then this factor

01:02:35.650 --> 01:02:38.230
which determines the
spectrum of hydrogen

01:02:38.230 --> 01:02:41.890
is called the Rydberg constant
with an index H for hydrogen.

01:02:54.820 --> 01:03:00.752
You find the electronic
eigenfunctions

01:03:00.752 --> 01:03:05.040
as the solution of
Schrodinger's equation.

01:03:05.040 --> 01:03:12.050
And the eigenfunctions
have a simple angular part,

01:03:12.050 --> 01:03:14.205
which are the
spherical harmonics.

01:03:14.205 --> 01:03:16.410
We are not talking about that.

01:03:16.410 --> 01:03:19.590
But there is a radial
part, radial wave function.

01:03:30.950 --> 01:03:36.120
So if you solve it, if you
find those wave functions,

01:03:36.120 --> 01:03:40.240
there are a number of
noteworthy results.

01:03:40.240 --> 01:03:45.180
One is in short form the
spectrum is the Rydberg

01:03:45.180 --> 01:03:47.020
constant divided by n squared.

01:03:50.750 --> 01:03:56.230
I want to talk to you
about your intuition

01:03:56.230 --> 01:03:58.330
for the size of
the hydrogen atom,

01:03:58.330 --> 01:04:01.910
or for the size of
hydrogen-like atoms.

01:04:01.910 --> 01:04:07.290
So what I want to discuss
is several important aspects

01:04:07.290 --> 01:04:10.380
about the radius or
the expectation value

01:04:10.380 --> 01:04:13.420
of the position of the electron.

01:04:13.420 --> 01:04:16.620
And it's important
to distinguish

01:04:16.620 --> 01:04:19.530
between the expectation
value for the radius

01:04:19.530 --> 01:04:21.160
and the inverse radius.

01:04:25.210 --> 01:04:27.830
The expectation
value for the radius

01:04:27.830 --> 01:04:34.400
is, well, a little
bit more complicated.

01:04:34.400 --> 01:04:41.070
1/2 1 minus l times l
plus 1 over n squared.

01:04:44.200 --> 01:04:54.000
Whereas, the result for the
inverse radius is very simple.

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:58.480
What I've introduced here
is the natural length scale

01:04:58.480 --> 01:05:04.950
for the hydrogen atom
which is the Bohr radius.

01:05:04.950 --> 01:05:11.322
And just to be general,
mu is the reduced mass.

01:05:11.322 --> 01:05:12.780
So it's close to
the electron mass.

01:05:21.560 --> 01:05:26.400
Well, the one thing I
want to discuss with you--

01:05:26.400 --> 01:05:34.020
we will need leader for the
discussion of quantum defects,

01:05:34.020 --> 01:05:37.430
for field ionization
and other processes,

01:05:37.430 --> 01:05:41.610
we have to know what the
size of the wave function is.

01:05:41.610 --> 01:05:44.900
And so usually, if
you wave your hands,

01:05:44.900 --> 01:05:48.260
you would say the
expectation value of 1/r

01:05:48.260 --> 01:05:50.920
is 1 over the
expectation value or r.

01:05:50.920 --> 01:05:54.680
But there are now some
important differences.

01:05:54.680 --> 01:05:56.500
I first want to
sort of ask you, why

01:05:56.500 --> 01:05:59.160
is the expectation
value of 1/r, why

01:05:59.160 --> 01:06:01.178
does it have this
very, very simple form?

01:06:05.825 --> 01:06:06.866
AUDIENCE: Virial theorem?

01:06:06.866 --> 01:06:08.900
PROFESSOR: The Virial theorem.

01:06:08.900 --> 01:06:10.590
Yes.

01:06:10.590 --> 01:06:15.360
We know that there is a fairly
simple form for the energy

01:06:15.360 --> 01:06:16.090
eigenvalues.

01:06:16.090 --> 01:06:18.460
It's 1 over n squared.

01:06:18.460 --> 01:06:23.810
Well, Coulomb energy
e square over r.

01:06:23.810 --> 01:06:26.880
So if the only energy
of the hydrogen atom

01:06:26.880 --> 01:06:29.250
were Coulomb energy,
it's very clear

01:06:29.250 --> 01:06:32.700
that 1/r, which is proportional
to the Coulomb energy,

01:06:32.700 --> 01:06:37.780
has to have the same simple
form as the energy eigenvalue.

01:06:37.780 --> 01:06:39.860
Well, there is a
second contribution

01:06:39.860 --> 01:06:42.130
to the energy in addition
to Coulomb energy.

01:06:42.130 --> 01:06:43.620
This is kinetic energy.

01:06:43.620 --> 01:06:47.240
But due to the Virial
theorem, the kinetic energy

01:06:47.240 --> 01:06:50.030
is actually proportional
to the Coulomb energy.

01:06:50.030 --> 01:06:54.570
And therefore, the total
energy is proportional to 1/r.

01:06:54.570 --> 01:07:00.690
And therefore, 1/r has to
scale exactly as the energy.

01:07:00.690 --> 01:07:05.990
Since the energy until we
introduce fine structure is

01:07:05.990 --> 01:07:09.530
independent of l, only depends
on the principal quantum number

01:07:09.530 --> 01:07:12.730
n, we find there's
only an n-dependence.

01:07:12.730 --> 01:07:15.510
But if you would ask, what
is the expectation value

01:07:15.510 --> 01:07:16.600
for the radius?

01:07:16.600 --> 01:07:18.750
You find an l-dependence
because you're

01:07:18.750 --> 01:07:20.710
talking about a very
different quantity.

01:07:23.640 --> 01:07:29.830
So let me just summarize
what we just discussed.

01:07:29.830 --> 01:07:35.680
We have the Virial
theorem, which

01:07:35.680 --> 01:07:40.350
in general is of
the following form.

01:07:40.350 --> 01:07:42.630
If you have potential
energy which

01:07:42.630 --> 01:07:48.990
is proportional to
radius to the n,

01:07:48.990 --> 01:07:55.010
then the expectation value
for the kinetic energy

01:07:55.010 --> 01:08:00.540
is n/2 times the expectation
value for the potential energy.

01:08:00.540 --> 01:08:02.800
The most famous
example is n equals

01:08:02.800 --> 01:08:04.120
2, the harmonic oscillator.

01:08:04.120 --> 01:08:07.710
You have an equal contribution
to potential energy

01:08:07.710 --> 01:08:10.430
of the spring and
kinetic energy.

01:08:10.430 --> 01:08:12.710
Well, here for the
Coulomb problem,

01:08:12.710 --> 01:08:17.020
we discuss n equals minus 1.

01:08:17.020 --> 01:08:20.390
And therefore,
the kinetic energy

01:08:20.390 --> 01:08:24.386
is minus 1/2 times
the potential energy.

01:08:32.670 --> 01:08:41.420
So this factor of 2 appears
now in a number of relations

01:08:41.420 --> 01:08:46.670
and that's as follows.

01:08:46.670 --> 01:08:50.670
If you take the
Rydberg constant,

01:08:50.670 --> 01:08:54.970
the Rydberg constant
in CGS units

01:08:54.970 --> 01:09:03.210
is-- well, that's the Coulomb
energy at the Bohr radius.

01:09:03.210 --> 01:09:05.970
But the Rydberg
constant is 1/2 of it.

01:09:09.069 --> 01:09:22.069
So the Rydberg constant is
1/2 of another quantity,

01:09:22.069 --> 01:09:26.050
which is called 1 Hartree.

01:09:26.050 --> 01:09:27.990
We'll talk, probably
not , today,

01:09:27.990 --> 01:09:33.040
but on Monday
about atomic units,

01:09:33.040 --> 01:09:36.710
about sort of fundamental
system of units.

01:09:36.710 --> 01:09:40.750
And the fundamental way--
the fundamental energy

01:09:40.750 --> 01:09:44.490
of the hydrogen atom, the
fundamental unit of energy

01:09:44.490 --> 01:09:49.609
is whatever energy
you can construct

01:09:49.609 --> 01:09:53.590
using the electron mass, the
electron charge, and h bar.

01:09:53.590 --> 01:09:56.670
And what you get is 1 Hartree.

01:09:56.670 --> 01:10:02.180
If you ever wondered why the
Rydberg is 1/2 Hartree, what

01:10:02.180 --> 01:10:05.350
happens is in the ground
state of hydrogen,

01:10:05.350 --> 01:10:10.280
you have 1 Hartree
worth of Coulomb energy.

01:10:10.280 --> 01:10:14.720
But then because of the Virial
theorem, you have minus 1/2

01:10:14.720 --> 01:10:16.870
of it as kinetic energy.

01:10:16.870 --> 01:10:19.767
And therefore, the
binding energy in the n

01:10:19.767 --> 01:10:23.770
equals 1 ground state,
which is 1 Rydberg,

01:10:23.770 --> 01:10:25.810
is 1/2 of the Hartree.

01:10:25.810 --> 01:10:28.620
So this factor of 1/2
of the Virial theorem

01:10:28.620 --> 01:10:32.165
is responsible for this factor
of 2 for those two energies.

01:10:35.580 --> 01:10:39.120
I usually prefer SI units
for all calculations,

01:10:39.120 --> 01:10:46.710
but there's certain relations
where we should use CGS units.

01:10:46.710 --> 01:10:50.550
Just as a side remark, if
you want to go to SI units,

01:10:50.550 --> 01:10:53.860
you simply replace
the electron charge e

01:10:53.860 --> 01:10:57.440
squared by e squared
divided by 4 pi epsilon0.

01:11:10.851 --> 01:11:11.350
OK.

01:11:11.350 --> 01:11:15.010
So I've discussed
the hydrogen atom.

01:11:15.010 --> 01:11:18.860
It's also insightful
and you should actually

01:11:18.860 --> 01:11:22.950
remember that or be able to
re-derive it for yourself.

01:11:22.950 --> 01:11:29.210
How do things depend on
the nuclear charge z?

01:11:29.210 --> 01:11:32.120
Well, if you have
a nuclear charge z,

01:11:32.120 --> 01:11:39.430
the Coulomb energy
goes up by-- well,

01:11:39.430 --> 01:11:41.020
if you have a
stronger attraction.

01:11:41.020 --> 01:11:48.570
If you would go to helium
nucleus or even more

01:11:48.570 --> 01:11:51.110
highly-charged nucleus and
put one electron in it.

01:11:51.110 --> 01:11:54.240
Because of the stronger
Coulomb attraction,

01:11:54.240 --> 01:11:58.315
all the length scales
are divided by z.

01:12:00.890 --> 01:12:04.590
So everything is smaller
by a factor of z.

01:12:04.590 --> 01:12:06.750
So what does that now
imply for the energy?

01:12:09.340 --> 01:12:13.260
Well, you have a Coulomb field
which is z times stronger,

01:12:13.260 --> 01:12:17.330
but you probe it now at
a z times smaller radius.

01:12:17.330 --> 01:12:22.469
So therefore, the energies
scale with z squared.

01:12:45.000 --> 01:12:50.510
Let me formulate a question
because we need that later on.

01:12:50.510 --> 01:12:57.790
So if you have a
hydrogen-like atom

01:12:57.790 --> 01:13:00.850
and the electron is in a state
with principal quantum number

01:13:00.850 --> 01:13:02.040
n.

01:13:02.040 --> 01:13:04.080
And let's assume there
is no angular momentum.

01:13:07.280 --> 01:13:11.330
So what I'm writing down
for you is the probability

01:13:11.330 --> 01:13:14.470
for the electron to
be at the nucleus.

01:13:14.470 --> 01:13:16.170
This will be very
important later on

01:13:16.170 --> 01:13:19.880
when ewe discuss hyperfine
structure because hyperfine

01:13:19.880 --> 01:13:23.600
is responsible-- for
hyperfine structure, what

01:13:23.600 --> 01:13:28.630
is responsible is the fact
that the electron can overlap

01:13:28.630 --> 01:13:29.850
with the nucleus.

01:13:29.850 --> 01:13:32.280
So this factor will
appear in our discussion

01:13:32.280 --> 01:13:34.570
of hyperfine structure.

01:13:34.570 --> 01:13:43.740
And what I want to ask you is,
how does this quantity depend

01:13:43.740 --> 01:13:48.800
on the principal quantum
number n and on z?

01:13:54.190 --> 01:13:56.470
And I want to give
you four choices.

01:14:18.760 --> 01:14:21.570
Of course, for
dimensional reasons,

01:14:21.570 --> 01:14:23.480
everything is 1
over the Bohr radius

01:14:23.480 --> 01:14:25.970
cubed because it's a density.

01:14:25.970 --> 01:14:30.250
But you cannot use
dimensional analysis to guess,

01:14:30.250 --> 01:14:36.550
how do things scale
with z and with n?

01:14:36.550 --> 01:14:42.480
So here are your four choices.

01:14:42.480 --> 01:14:46.290
Does it scale with z,
z squared, z cubed?

01:14:46.290 --> 01:14:50.712
Does it scale with n
squared, n cubed, n to the 6?

01:15:03.320 --> 01:15:05.884
If you don't know it,
just make your best guess.

01:15:19.540 --> 01:15:23.240
OK, one part should be
relatively straightforward.

01:15:23.240 --> 01:15:25.700
And this is the scaling with z.

01:15:25.700 --> 01:15:27.440
Let me just stop it.

01:15:31.930 --> 01:15:49.040
So the exact answer is that z n
00 at the origin squared is pi

01:15:49.040 --> 01:15:50.960
a0 cubed.

01:15:50.960 --> 01:15:55.840
And its c cubed over n cubed.

01:15:55.840 --> 01:15:59.745
So the correct
answer is this one.

01:16:02.430 --> 01:16:11.190
Let me first say-- OK,
I gave you four choices

01:16:11.190 --> 01:16:16.460
and it's difficult to
distinguish all of them.

01:16:16.460 --> 01:16:20.200
But the first one you should
have gotten rather simply,

01:16:20.200 --> 01:16:23.590
and this is the z-scaling.

01:16:23.590 --> 01:16:30.436
Because the scaling
with z is the following,

01:16:30.436 --> 01:16:35.120
that everything-- if you write
down the Schrodinger equation,

01:16:35.120 --> 01:16:40.230
if you have z, you replace
e squared by z e squared.

01:16:40.230 --> 01:16:43.340
And I actually just mentioned
it five minutes ago,

01:16:43.340 --> 01:16:48.850
that all length scales, the
Bohr radius is h bar squared

01:16:48.850 --> 01:16:51.970
over electron mass
times e squared.

01:16:51.970 --> 01:16:55.290
It actually scales with 1/z.

01:16:55.290 --> 01:16:58.990
So if all length
scales go as 1/z,

01:16:58.990 --> 01:17:05.410
the density goes with z cubed.

01:17:05.410 --> 01:17:08.155
So therefore, one should
have immediately narrowed

01:17:08.155 --> 01:17:09.015
down the choice.

01:17:11.520 --> 01:17:13.150
It should be A or
C because they have

01:17:13.150 --> 01:17:15.450
the correct scaling with z.

01:17:15.450 --> 01:17:17.580
The scaling with
n is more subtle

01:17:17.580 --> 01:17:20.980
and there was something
surprising I learned about it.

01:17:20.980 --> 01:17:25.710
And this is what
I want to present

01:17:25.710 --> 01:17:28.780
to you in the last
three or four minutes.

01:17:28.780 --> 01:17:32.280
So the z-scaling, just remember
that the length scaling

01:17:32.280 --> 01:17:34.450
is the length scales as 1/z.

01:17:34.450 --> 01:17:36.140
Therefore, density
scale was z cubed.

01:17:40.010 --> 01:17:42.460
The interesting thing
about the length scaling

01:17:42.460 --> 01:17:44.990
is-- and I just want to draw
your attention to it because it

01:17:44.990 --> 01:17:49.460
can be confusing,
that in high torsion

01:17:49.460 --> 01:17:55.240
we have not only one length
scale, but two length scales.

01:17:55.240 --> 01:17:57.380
We have mentioned
one of it already,

01:17:57.380 --> 01:18:01.380
which is the energetic
length scale 1/r.

01:18:01.380 --> 01:18:05.680
1/r is the Coulomb energy.

01:18:05.680 --> 01:18:07.450
Because of the
Virial theorem, it's

01:18:07.450 --> 01:18:09.611
proportional to
the total energy.

01:18:09.611 --> 01:18:12.110
And that's what you know, what
you remember when you wake up

01:18:12.110 --> 01:18:14.450
in the middle of the
night out of deep sleep,

01:18:14.450 --> 01:18:20.030
that the energy of high
torsion is 1 over n squared.

01:18:20.030 --> 01:18:25.850
So therefore, this
is a0 over n squared.

01:18:25.850 --> 01:18:33.440
However, if you look at the
wave function of hydrogen,

01:18:33.440 --> 01:18:35.880
you factor out.

01:18:35.880 --> 01:18:38.120
When you solve the
radial equation,

01:18:38.120 --> 01:18:39.790
you factor out an exponential.

01:18:39.790 --> 01:18:41.870
There's sort of
polynomial and then

01:18:41.870 --> 01:18:44.430
there is an exponential decay.

01:18:44.430 --> 01:19:03.080
And the characteristic lengths
in the exponential decay

01:19:03.080 --> 01:19:13.540
of the wave function
is n e0 over z.

01:19:18.010 --> 01:19:22.200
So therefore, when we
talk about wave functions

01:19:22.200 --> 01:19:26.260
with principal quantum number
n, there are two length scale.

01:19:26.260 --> 01:19:32.140
1 over r n l scales
with n squared.

01:19:32.140 --> 01:19:34.740
But the characteristic
length scale

01:19:34.740 --> 01:19:36.880
in the exponential
part of the radial wave

01:19:36.880 --> 01:19:43.760
function scales with n
and not with n squared.

01:19:48.450 --> 01:19:52.330
And it is this exponential
part of the wave function

01:19:52.330 --> 01:20:00.690
which scales with n which is
responsible for the probability

01:20:00.690 --> 01:20:02.850
to find the electron
as the nucleus.

01:20:02.850 --> 01:20:06.850
Which, as I said before,
the z-scaling is simple

01:20:06.850 --> 01:20:09.630
but the n-scaling
is not n to the 6.

01:20:09.630 --> 01:20:11.130
It's n cubed.

01:20:18.630 --> 01:20:22.680
And this is really important.

01:20:22.680 --> 01:20:29.680
And this describes the
scaling with n for everything

01:20:29.680 --> 01:20:34.600
which depends on the presence
of the electron as a nucleus.

01:20:34.600 --> 01:20:37.510
One is the quantum
defect and the other one

01:20:37.510 --> 01:20:39.140
is the hyperfine structure.

01:20:43.940 --> 01:20:47.670
Let me just give you
one more scaling.

01:20:47.670 --> 01:20:50.200
I've discussed now what
happens for 0 angular

01:20:50.200 --> 01:20:54.030
momentum, for finite
angular momentum states,

01:20:54.030 --> 01:20:57.620
psi is proportional
to r to the l.

01:20:57.620 --> 01:21:03.640
So therefore, if you
ask, what is psi square,

01:21:03.640 --> 01:21:06.450
it scales with 2l.

01:21:06.450 --> 01:21:11.100
And at least for
large n, the n-scaling

01:21:11.100 --> 01:21:13.996
is, again, 1 over n cubed.

01:21:20.190 --> 01:21:22.747
OK, that's what I wanted
to present you today.

